LOCUS       LPETG_tag                  5 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  LPETG — the canonical sortase A (SrtA) recognition motif (a single
            instance of the Gram-positive LPXTG cell-wall sorting signal); SrtA
            cleaves between the Thr and Gly (LPET|G), forming an acyl-enzyme
            thioester that is resolved by transpeptidation onto an N-terminal
            oligoglycine acceptor, making LPETG the standard C-terminal handle
            for site-specific protein ligation (sortagging) and conjugation..
