                     /synonym="LPETG"
                     /note="Sortase A (SrtA) recognition motif and a single
                     instance of the Gram-positive LPXTG cell-wall sorting
                     signal (Leu-Pro-Glu-Thr-Gly). SrtA cleaves the scissile
                     peptide bond between the P1 Thr and the P1' Gly (LPET|G),
                     forming a covalent acyl-enzyme thioester intermediate at
                     the active-site Cys; this intermediate is resolved by
                     nucleophilic attack of an N-terminal oligoglycine (Gly-n,
                     typically GGG/GGGGG) acceptor, ligating the upstream
                     protein to the acceptor and regenerating an LPETGG...
                     junction. Whole-part feature spanning all 5 residues; this
                     is a single atomic functional element with no functional
                     sub-features. The X position of the LPXTG consensus is most
                     commonly Glu (E) in efficient engineering substrates.
                     Source-verified to UniProt P02976 (Protein A) Motif 'LPXTG
                     sorting signal' at positions 482-486, 5/5 identity."
